Vice President Mike Pence held an organizational call with members of the Presidential Advisory Commission on Election Integrity. The commission has been tasked with producing recommendations to increase the American people's confidence in the integrity of the election systems. The first meeting of the commission is set for July 19 in Washington, D.C. Vice Chair Kris Kobach announced that a letter will be sent to all 50 states and the District of Columbia requesting publicly-available data from state voter rolls and feedback on how to improve election integrity.